cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it proposes a novel approach for abnormality classification in chest X-ray images using location aware Dense Networks. It also utilizes high-resolution images and spatial information to improve performance. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, to train the model, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. 

As the paper deals with medical imaging and pathology classification, it could also belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) category. 

The paper involves the use of algorithms and tools to support the reading workflow and reduce reading errors, which makes it likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. 

Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method on a large data set, which could make it relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category.
